Type the second function:

def load_score():
    file = open("score.txt", "r")
    return file.read()

Same open, but the mode is "r" for READ — give back what's in the file, don't change anything. file.read pulls every character of the file into one string. return hands that string back to whoever called load_score. We could call file.close after reading, but for short reads inside a function Python tidies up on its own.
